Title: Toda lattice realization of integrable hierarchies
Authors: L.Bonora, C.P.Constantinidis, E.Vinteler
Comments: 11 pages, Latex (minor changes, to appear in Lett.Math.Phys.)
Report-no: SISSA 144/95/EP, IFT-P057/95
Journal-ref: Lett.Math.Phys. 38 (1996) 349-363
\\
  We present a new realization of scalar integrable hierarchies in terms of the
Toda lattice hierarchy. In other words, we show on a large number of examples
that an integrable hierarchy, defined by a pseudodifferential Lax operator, can
be embedded in the Toda lattice hierarchy. Such a realization in terms the Toda
lattice hierarchy seems to be as general as the Drinfeld--Sokolov realization.
